snippet.textDisplay: New album from Niall Horan is what I''ve been waiting all this time. Flicker is a dreamlike and a great album that I've kept listening for years after it was released on mid-October 2017. It sets a tone what state of mind I was in during that time. I'll never forget how that album makes my heart felt like I was in a secluded place imagining scenarios that I would wanted myself to be, or daydreaming I was in a romantic or safest place - not feeling even a bit of discomfort. It was a complete bliss. I've learned to seize every moment, and not missed a single moment despite of unexpected obstacles. I've learned to feel and appreciate my surroundings, and why is that I appreciated listening to Flicker because I've learned to accept who I am, and embrace my emotions whether it is overwhelming or underwhelming. When I listen to that album- I feel like I'm less lonely person in the world because I'd get to experience what this album speaks, and what in-stored in it. I'm looking forward to 'Heartbreak Weather' and I'm sure I would get to experience another kind of bliss when it's finally dropped. Thanks for taking your time to read this. I know it's a long comment, it's how long I speak when something's got a special place in my heart, and if there's one thing that sparks my mind.
